{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_28a804f68ffe9QB31FosW6aSKr","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d757fd773001cOeTVse8iKV0xr","parts":[{"id":"prt_d757fe140001YwBTybzOFdyeQZ","messageID":"msg_d757fd773001cOeTVse8iKV0xr","sessionID":"ses_28a804f68ffe9QB31FosW6aSKr","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ad52fc401d5a4e3b983a938e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md"},"output":"<path>/workspace/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: ![Logo](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/piccolo-orm/piccolo/master/docs/logo_hero.png \"Piccolo Logo\")\n2: \n3: ![Tests](https://github.com/piccolo-orm/piccolo/actions/workflows/tests.yaml/badge.svg)\n4: ![Release](https://github.com/piccolo-orm/piccolo/actions/workflows/release.yaml/badge.svg)\n5: [![Documentation Status](https://readthedocs.org/projects/piccolo-orm/badge/?version=latest)](https://piccolo-orm.readthedocs.io/en/latest/?badge=latest)\n6: [![PyPI](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/piccolo?color=%2334D058&label=pypi)](https://pypi.org/project/piccolo/)\n7: [![codecov](https://codecov.io/gh/piccolo-orm/piccolo/branch/master/graph/badge.svg?token=V19CWH7MXX)](https://codecov.io/gh/piccolo-orm/piccolo)\n8: \n9: Piccolo is a fast, user friendly ORM and query builder which supports asyncio. [Read the docs](https://piccolo-orm.readthedocs.io/en/latest/).\n10: \n11: ## Features\n12: \n13: Some of it’s stand out features are:\n14: \n15: - Support for sync and async.\n16: - A builtin playground, which makes learning a breeze.\n17: - Tab completion support - works great with iPython and VSCode.\n18: - Batteries included - a User model, authentication, migrations, an [admin GUI](https://github.com/piccolo-orm/piccolo_admin), and more.\n19: - Modern Python - fully type annotated.\n20: - Make your codebase modular and scalable with Piccolo apps (similar to Django apps).\n21: \n22: ## Syntax\n23: \n24: The syntax is clean and expressive.\n25: \n26: You can use it as a query builder:\n27: \n28: ```python\n29: # Select:\n30: await Band.select(\n31:     Band.name\n32: ).where(\n33:     Band.popularity > 100\n34: )\n35: \n36: # Join:\n37: await Band.select(\n38:     Band.name,\n39:     Band.manager.name\n40: )\n41: \n42: # Delete:\n43: await Band.delete().where(\n44:     Band.popularity < 1000\n45: )\n46: \n47: # Update:\n48: await Band.update({Band.popularity: 10000}).where(\n49:     Band.name == 'Pythonistas'\n50: )\n51: ```\n52: \n53: Or like a typical ORM:\n54: \n55: ```python\n56: # To create a new object:\n57: b = Band(name='C-Sharps', popularity=100)\n58: await b.save()\n59: \n60: # To fetch an object from the database, and update it:\n61: b = await Band.objects().get(Band.name == 'Pythonistas')\n62: b.popularity = 10000\n63: await b.save()\n64: \n65: # To delete:\n66: await b.remove()\n67: ```\n68: \n69: ## Installation\n70: \n71: Installing with PostgreSQL driver:\n72: \n73: ```bash\n74: pip install 'piccolo[postgres]'\n75: ```\n76: \n77: Installing with SQLite driver:\n78: \n79: ```bash\n80: pip install 'piccolo[sqlite]'\n81: ```\n82: \n83: Installing with all optional dependencies (easiest):\n84: \n85: ```bash\n86: pip install 'piccolo[all]'\n87: ```\n88: \n89: ## Building a web app?\n90: \n91: Let Piccolo scaffold you an ASGI web app, using Piccolo as the ORM:\n92: \n93: ```bash\n94: piccolo asgi new\n95: ```\n96: \n97: [Starlette](https://www.starlette.io/), [FastAPI](https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/), [BlackSheep](https://www.neoteroi.dev/blacksheep/), [Litestar](https://litestar.dev/), [Ravyn](https://www.ravyn.dev/), [Lilya](https://lilya.dev/), [Quart](https://quart.palletsprojects.com/en/latest/), [Falcon](https://falconframework.org/) and [Sanic](https://sanic.dev/en/) are currently supported.\n98: \n99: ## Piccolo ecosystem\n100: \n101: ### Piccolo Admin\n102: \n103: Piccolo Admin is a powerful admin interface / content management system for Python, built on top of Piccolo.\n104: \n105: It was created at a design agency to serve the needs of customers who demand a high quality, beautiful admin interface for their websites. It's a modern alternative to tools like Wordpress and Django Admin.\n106: \n107: It's built using the latest technologies, with Vue.js on the front end, and a powerful REST backend.\n108: \n109: Some of it's standout features:\n110: \n111: * Powerful data filtering\n112: * Builtin security\n113: * Multi-factor Authentication\n114: * Media support, both locally and in S3 compatible services\n115: * Dark mode support\n116: * CSV exports\n117: * Easily create custom forms\n118: * Works on mobile and desktop\n119: * Use standalone, or integrate with several supported ASGI frameworks\n120: * Multilingual out of box\n121: * Bulk actions, like updating and deleting data\n122: * Flexible UI - only show the columns you want your users to see\n123: \n124: You can read the docs [here](https://piccolo-admin.readthedocs.io/en/latest/).\n125: \n126: ### Piccolo API\n127: \n128: Utilities for easily exposing [Piccolo](https://piccolo-orm.readthedocs.io/en/latest/) tables as REST endpoints in ASGI apps, such as [Starlette](https://www.starlette.io) and [FastAPI](https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/).\n129: \n130: Includes a bunch of useful ASGI middleware:\n131: \n132: - Session Auth\n133: - Token Auth\n134: - Rate Limiting\n135: - CSRF\n136: - Content Security Policy (CSP)\n137: - And more\n138: \n139: You can read the docs [here](https://piccolo-api.readthedocs.io/en/latest/).\n140: \n141: ## Are you a Django user?\n142: \n143: We have a handy page which shows the equivalent of [common Django queries in Piccolo](https://piccolo-orm.readthedocs.io/en/latest/piccolo/query_types/django_comparison.html).\n144: \n145: ## Documentation\n146: \n147: Our documentation is on [Read the docs](https://piccolo-orm.readthedocs.io/en/latest/piccolo/getting_started/index.html).\n148: \n149: We also have some great [tutorial videos on YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCE7x5nm1Iy9KDfXPNrNQ5lA).\n\n(End of file - total 149 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"![Logo](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/piccolo-orm/piccolo/master/docs/logo_hero.png \"Piccolo Logo\")\n\n![Tests](https://github.com/piccolo-orm/piccolo/actions/workflows/tests.yaml/badge.svg)\n![Release](https://github.com/piccolo-orm/piccolo/actions/workflows/release.yaml/badge.svg)\n[![Documentation Status](https://readthedocs.org/projects/piccolo-orm/badge/?version=latest)](https://piccolo-orm.readthedocs.io/en/latest/?badge=latest)\n[![PyPI](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/piccolo?color=%2334D058&label=pypi)](https://pypi.org/project/piccolo/)\n[![codecov](https://codecov.io/gh/piccolo-orm/piccolo/branch/master/graph/badge.svg?token=V19CWH7MXX)](https://codecov.io/gh/piccolo-orm/piccolo)\n\nPiccolo is a fast, user friendly ORM and query builder which supports asyncio. [Read the docs](https://piccolo-orm.readthedocs.io/en/latest/).\n\n## Features\n\nSome of it’s stand out features are:\n\n- Support for sync and async.\n- A builtin playground, which makes learning a breeze.\n- Tab completion support - works great with iPython and VSCode.\n- Batteries included - a User model, authentication, migrations, an [admin GUI](https://github.com/piccolo-orm/piccolo_admin), and more.\n- Modern Python - fully type annotated.\n- Make your codebase modular and scalable with Piccolo apps (similar to Django apps).","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"README.md","time":{"start":1775792808663,"end":1775792808673}}}]}
